      • scope_FDField_target

        public org.eclipse.xtext.scoping.IScope scope_FDField_target(FDCompoundOverwrites ctxt,
                                                    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EReference ref)
        Compute the target elements (of type FField) for a given FDField, if the FDField is a child of a FDCompoundOverwrites section.

        I.e., ctxt will be either a struct overwrite section or a union overwrite section. The actual available fields depend on the Franca type of the target element of the overwrite section's parent.

      • scope_FDProperty_decl

        public org.eclipse.xtext.scoping.IScope scope_FDProperty_decl(FDTypeOverwrites owner,
                                                     org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EReference ref)
        The properties of an overwrite section are determined by the Franca type of the parent element (i.e., container element in the deployment definition model hierarchy).

        Example: In a FDStructOverwrites section, the parent element might be for example a FDAttribute. Validation will ensure that the Franca type of the FDAttribute target (which is an FAttribute) is an FStructType. Thus, the properties we are looking for here are all struct-related properties from the deployment specification.
